# ChatGPT Backend

A ChatGPT-style backend built with **Django** and **Django REST Framework (DRF)**. It handles
users, projects, conversations, messages (with file attachments), AI-model and assistant
selection, JWT authentication, subscriptions with daily rate limiting, and quick account
switching. AI replies are mocked (fixed text that names the selected model).

## Tech stack
- Django + Django REST Framework
- SimpleJWT (authentication)
- drf-spectacular (OpenAPI / Swagger docs)
- SQLite

## Setup

```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate            # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

python manage.py migrate
python manage.py createsuperuser    # needed to manage AI models
python manage.py runserver
```

## API documentation (Swagger)

Interactive docs — browse and test every endpoint here:

**http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/docs/**

Raw OpenAPI schema: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/schema/`

### Authenticating in Swagger
1. `POST /api/auth/register/` to create a user.
2. `POST /api/auth/login/` to get an `access` token.
3. Click **Authorize** (top right) and enter `Bearer <access-token>`.

## Endpoints overview

| Area | Endpoint |
|------|----------|
| Auth | `POST /api/auth/register/`, `POST /api/auth/login/`, `GET|PATCH /api/auth/profile/` |
| Account switching | `POST /api/auth/account-link/`, `GET /api/auth/linked-accounts/`, `POST /api/auth/switch/` |
| Projects | `GET|POST /api/projects/`, `.../<id>/`, `GET /api/projects/<id>/conversations/` |
| Conversations | `GET|POST /api/conversations/`, `.../<id>/` |
| Messages | `GET|POST /api/conversations/<id>/messages/` |
| Attachments | `GET /api/messages/<id>/attachments/` |
| Assistants | `GET|POST /api/assistants/`, `.../<id>/` |
| AI models | `GET /api/models/` (read-only; superuser may modify) |
| Subscription | `GET /api/subscription/status/`, `GET /api/subscription/plans/`, `POST /api/subscription/purchase/` |

## Running tests

```bash
python manage.py test
```

48 tests cover authentication, per-user data isolation, soft-delete, the message/mock-reply
flow, file attachments, subscription limits, throttling, and account switching.

## Notes
- Free users are limited to 50 messages/day (enforced with DRF throttling); premium users are unlimited.
- Deleting a conversation is a soft-delete (its status becomes `deleted`; the row is kept).
- A conversation requires an AI model, so seed at least one (via the admin or superuser `POST /api/models/`) before creating conversations.